<seg id=1> The collision of a train and a bus at a railroad and public road crossing that occurred in the town of Danbard in the eastern Indian state of Bihar has resulted in ten dead and 50 injured. </seg>
<seg id=2> A report by the Indian Newspaper Industry Trust of the Indian Communications Co. says that railroad officials blame passengers on the bus for the incident. </seg>
<seg id=3> The report says that passengers in a hurry took the key from the guard at the gate to the crossing and opened the gate. </seg>
<seg id=4> However, the train arrived before the bus had cleared the tracks, resulting in a collision between the train and the bus. </seg>
<seg id=5> All the dead were passengers on the bus. </seg>
</p>
